entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: hi i am ellie thanks for coming in today i was created to talk to people in a safe and secure environment i am not a therapist but i am here to learn about people and would love to learn about you i will ask a few questions to get us started and please feel free to tell me anything your answers are totally confidential are you ok with this

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes i am okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay so how are you doing today

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am good i am a little tired but i am good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good where are you from originally

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: michigan i am from michigan

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: really when did you move to la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: a long time ago then i left

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: something that i could erase from my memory probably a friend who i was dating i would like to erase from my memory how he responded to me when i told him my grandmother was ill

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is easy if i am busy all day and i am really really tired but actually my mind spins so it is not that easy actually it is not that easy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i would have to because i have to be exhausted i have to be exhausted

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: to be exhausted no it is not really hard you just do a lot of stuff all day long

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: irritable

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: up and down up and up and down like sometimes i have been excited and anxious and on the other side i am like what am i doing

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah it is just an anxiousness to wanna make some things happen some goals and

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: like what

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: getting certain kind of work and having a certain amount of income and just taking care of myself you know the way i think i should take care of myself just the physical stuff

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: sometimes i have a lot of distracting thoughts that have nothing to do with what i need to be focused on in the moment and i am conscious of that i am like of all the things that is popping up in my head why am i thinking about that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i i let them happen and then i i try to think about other things and phase it out it pops back up i phase it out yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: when the rooate moved out i was really happy when she finally left

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me how you spend your ideal weekend

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: probably reading and maybe go out go dancing that would be ideal i can go dancing go salsa dancing and yeah
